.TH "__bond_opt_set_notify" 9 "__bond_opt_set_notify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__bond_opt_set_notify \- set a bonding option
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __bond_opt_set_notify
.BI "(struct bonding *bond "  ","
.BI "unsigned int option "  ","
.BI "struct bond_opt_value *val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bond" 12
target bond device
.IP "option" 12
option to set
.IP "val" 12
value to set it to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to change the bond's option value and trigger
a notification to user sapce. It can be used for both enabling/changing
an option and for disabling it. RTNL lock must be obtained before calling
this function.
